- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics): The paper deals with the construction of a cellular automaton, which is a topic in discrete mathematics. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory): The concept of universality in cellular automata is related to information theory, as it involves the ability to simulate any other cellular automaton. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): The construction of a strongly universal cellular automaton involves logical reasoning and the manipulation of symbols. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper may be relevant to computational complexity theory, as the construction of a strongly universal cellular automaton involves determining the computational power of a particular system. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The construction of a cellular automaton involves the use of algorithms and data structures to manipulate the cells and their states.
